ith%20others'%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20gone%20to%20take%20a%20syringe%20to%20give%20an%20injection%20to%20a%20child.%20When%20I%20came%20back%2C%20I%20saw%20that%20the%20(oxygen)%20concentrator%20had%20caught%20fire.%20I%20called%20the%20ward%20boy%2C%20who%20came%20with%20the%20fire%20extinguisher%20and%20tried%20to%20put%20it%20out.%20But%20by%20then%2C%20the%20fire%20had%20spread%2C%26quot%3B%20Megha%20James%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEleven%20babies%20died%20in%20a%20fire%20that%20broke%20out%20at%20the%20Neonatal%20Intensive%20Care%20Unit%20of%20the%20Maharani%20Laxmi%20Bai%20Medical%20College%20in%20Jhansi%20Friday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaced%20with%20an%20enormous%20blaze%2C%20Megha%20James's%20mind%20worked%20with%20a%20frenetic%20speed%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20she%20cared%20little%20about%20burning%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20chappal%20caught%20fire%20and%20I%20burned%20my%20foot.%20Then%20my%20salwar%20caught%20fire.%20I%20removed%20my%20salwar%20and%20discarded%20it.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20my%20mind%20was%20virtually%20not%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20PTI%20Videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMegha%20James%20just%20wore%20another%20salwar%20and%20went%20back%20to%20the%20rescue%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20smoke%2C%20and%20once%20the%20lights%20went%20out%2C%20we%20could%20not%20see%20anything.%20The%20entire%20staff%20brought%20out%20at%20least%2014-15%20children.%20There%20were%2011%20beds%20in%20the%20ward%20with%2023-24%20babies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20the%20lights%20not%20gone%20out%20they%20could%20have%20saved%20more%20children%2C%20Megha%20James%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20all%20happened%20very%20suddenly.%20None%20of%20us%20had%20expected%20it.%26quot%3B%20Assistant%20Nursing%20Superintendent%20Nalini%20Sood%20praised%20Megha%20James's%20valour%20and%20recounted%20bits%20from%20how%20the%20rescue%20operation%20was%20carried%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hospital%20staff%20broke%20the%20glasses%20of%20the%20NICU%20ward%20to%20evacuate%20the%20babies.%20It%20was%20then%20Nurse%20Megha's%20salwar%20caught%20fire.%20Instead%20of%20caring%20for%20her%20safety%2C%20she%20stayed%20there%20to%20rescue%20the%20babies%20and%20handed%20them%20over%20to%20people%20outside%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENalini%20Sood%20said%20Megha%20James%20is%20currently%20undergoing%20treatment%20at%20the%20same%20medical%20college.%20She%20said%20she%20did%20not%20know%20the%20extent%20of%20her%20burns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rescued%20babies%20were%20shifted%20to%20a%20ward%20very%20close%20to%20the%20NICU%20ward...%20When%20I%20recall%20the%20scene%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20crying%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Anshul%20Jain%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20anaesthesiology%20department%20at%20the%20medical%20college%2C%20explained%20the%20standard%20rescue%20operation%20and%20claimed%20the%20hospital%20followed%20the%20protocol%20to%20the%20T.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20triage%20process%20during%20an%20ICU%20evacuation%2C%20the%20policy%20is%20to%20evacuate%20less-affected%20patients%20first.%20The%20rationale%20behind%20this%20approach%20is%20that%20patients%20requiring%20minimal%20support%20can%20be%20relocated%20quickly%2C%20enabling%20a%20larger%20number%20of%20evacuations%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20a%20shorter%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20contrast%2C%20patients%20on%20ventilators%20or%20requiring%20high%20oxygen%20support%20demand%20more%20time%20and%20resources%20for%20evacuation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20principle%20was%20successfully%20implemented%20in%20Jhansi%2C%20playing%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20saving%20many%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Anshul%20Jain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20newborn%20rescued%20from%20the%20fire%20died%20due%20to%20illness%20on%20Sunday%2C%20Jhansi%20