20a%20long%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamilies%20from%20rural%20or%20underserved%20areas%20need%20to%20travel%20long%20distances%20to%20reach%20hospitals%2C%20spending%20huge%20amounts%20on%20travel%20and%20stay%2C%20and%20often%20facing%20heartbreaking%20choices%20about%20work%2C%20income%2C%20and%20even%20relocating.%20Beyond%20the%20financial%20burden%2C%20the%20emotional%20toll%20on%20families%2C%20who%20may%20have%20to%20abandon%20work%20or%20uproot%20their%20lives%2C%20adds%20an%20overwhelming%20strain.%20This%20highlights%20the%20need%20for%20a%20comprehensive%20approach%20that%20addresses%20not%20only%20treatment%20but%20also%20support%20services%20for%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPrioritising%20early%20detection%20and%20affordable%20access%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20childhood%20cancer%2C%20early%20detection%20is%20key.%20Simple%20screenings%20and%20awareness%20programmes%20can%20detect%20cancer%20in%20kids%20before%20it%20spreads.%20However%2C%20we%20need%20to%20reach%20the%20rural%20and%20underserved%20areas%2C%20where%20there%E2%80%99s%20often%20little%20to%20no%20awareness%20about%20childhood%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrategies%20to%20support%20early%20detection%2C%20which%20can%20greatly%20improve%20outcomes%20for%20children%2C%20include%20empowering%20local%20practitioners%2C%20training%20community%20health%20workers%2C%20and%20collaborating%20with%20regional%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20medical%20intervention%20is%20essential%2C%20cancer%20care%20must%20be%20supplemented%20with%20financial%20and%20emotional%20support%20for%20families.%20Often%2C%20the%20costs%20associated%20with%20cancer%20treatment%20extend%20beyond%20medical%20bills%20%E2%80%94%20covering%20expenses%20like%20transportation%2C%20housing%20near%20treatment%20facilities%2C%20and%20income%20lost%20when%20parents%20must%20devote%20their%20time%20to%20caregiving.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20these%20needs%20through%20comprehensive%20support%20can%20improve%20both%20the%20survival%20rates%20and%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20these%20young%20patients%20and%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGovernment%20efforts%20in%20paediatric%20cancer%20care%3A%20The%20role%20of%20RBSK%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Family%20Welfare%2C%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20launched%20the%20Rashtriya%20Bal%20Swasthya%20Karyakram%20(RBSK)%20under%20the%20National%20Health%20Mission%20to%20provide%20comprehensive%20child%20health%20screening%20and%20early%20intervention%20services.%20This%20initiative%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20identifying%20health%20issues%20early%20and%20connecting%20children%20to%20the%20necessary%20care%20and%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECollaborating%20with%20private%20entities%20and%20non-profit%20organisations%20can%20elevate%20the%20RBSK%E2%80%99s%20success.%20Such%20partnerships%20enhance%20the%20programme%E2%80%99s%20reach%2C%20strengthen%20service%20delivery%2C%20and%20amplify%20its%20impact.%20By%20joining%20forces%2C%20the%20Government%2C%20private%20sector%2C%20and%20civil%20society%20can%20share%20resources%2C%20expand%20healthcare%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20ensure%20that%20every%20child%20receives%20the%20essential%20care%20they%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHonouring%20a%2015-year-long%20commitment%20to%20children%E2%80%99s%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20celebrate%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%2015th%20anniversary%20this%20year%2C%20we%20take%20stock%20of%20the%20path%20from%20our%20initial%20roots%20to%20our%20current%20extended%20paediatric%20care%20activities.%20Understanding%20that%20healthier%20children%20lead%20to%2